Let the width of the cross be $w.$  Then the area of the cross is equal to the area of the four red rectangles, minus the area of the four white squares, plus the area of the blue square.  Hence,
\[0.36s^2 = 4w(s - 2w) - 4w^2 + w^2.\]Solving, we find $w = \frac{s}{6}.$  The area of the blue square is then $\left( \frac{s}{6} \right)^2 = \frac{s^2}{36},$ so the blue area is $\frac{1}{s^2} \cdot \frac{s^2}{36} = \boxed{\frac{1}{36}}.$

